definitions.definition: A forefather, any of a person's direct ancestors.
An individual from whom one or more people (dynasty, tribe, nation...) are descended.
definitions.example: Abraham alias Ibrahim is the progenitor of both the Jewish and Arab peoples.

definitions.definition: An ancestral form of a species.
A predecessor of something, especially if also a precursor or model.
definitions.example: ARPANET was the progenitor of the Internet.
